# Quality Gates and Tooling

- Run and fix WordPress Coding Standards checks before finalizing (`phpcs` with WPCS).
- Treat security-relevant warnings as blockers, not informational suggestions.
- Run PHP syntax checks and JS/CSS linting on changed files.
- Prefer automated formatting/lint fixes where available, then review manually.
- Keep CI checks green before release; do not ignore failures without documented rationale.
- Add regression tests for fixed bugs and critical flows when test harness exists.
- For performance-sensitive changes, include before/after evidence (query count, TTFB, or asset size).
- Ensure build artifacts are reproducible and do not include local-only files.
